    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
                <!-- Mission Section -->
                <section class="about-section">
                    <div class="section-header">
                        <div class="section-icon">
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
                                <path d="M12 16v-4"></path>
                                <path d="M12 8h.01"></path>
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <h2 class="section-title" data-i18n="OurMission">Our Mission</h2>
                    </div>
                    <p class="section-content" data-i18n="OurMissionDesc">
                        At Kairos Weather, our mission is simple: to make weather information accessible, accurate, and easy to understand for everyone. We believe that weather plays a crucial role in daily life — from planning outdoor activities to ensuring safety during severe weather conditions.
                    </p>
                    <p class="section-content">
                        Weather touches almost every decision we make. Whether you are deciding what to wear, planning a journey, scheduling a harvest, organising an outdoor event, or simply wondering whether to carry an umbrella, reliable weather information helps you make better choices. Yet a lot of weather websites are cluttered, slow, or overloaded with jargon. We built Kairos Weather to be the opposite: a clean, fast, and genuinely helpful place to check conditions and forecasts for anywhere in the world.
                    </p>
                    <p class="section-content">
                        Beyond raw numbers, we also want to help people <em>understand</em> the weather. That is why we publish in-depth, easy-to-read guides on our <a href="/blog">weather blog</a> — covering how forecasting works, how to stay safe in extreme conditions, what humidity and wind chill really mean, how to read the clouds, and more. Our goal is not just to tell you today's temperature, but to help you become more weather-aware every day.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <!-- Features Grid -->
                <section class="about-section">
                    <div class="section-header">
                        <div class="section-icon">
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                                <polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"></polygon>
